results.name: Greatest prime contained as binary substring in binary representation of n>1, a(1)=1.
comment: for n>1: a(n) = n iff n is prime.
link: Reinhard Zumkeller, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
example: n=12 -> '1100' contains 2 binary substrings which are primes: '11' (11bb) and '10' (b11b); 3='11' is the greater one, therefore a(12)=3.
results.author: _Reinhard Zumkeller_, Dec 08 2002
